  "notes": [
    "This study uses Cushing's disease patients as a natural model to study the effects of prolonged high cortisol exposure on cognitive function in humans.",
    "The nomogram model incorporates four key risk factors: cortisol AM/PM ratio, 8 a.m. cortisol concentration, body mass index, and fasting plasma glucose.",
    "The study provides evidence for the mechanisms by which cortisol affects cognitive function through glucocorticoid and mineralocorticoid receptors in the hippocampus."
  ]
